{'GreenhouseDT': 'The GreenhouseDT system emphasizes **behavioral adaptation** between the physical greenhouse and its digital twin, but explicit fidelity requirements (e.g., model accuracy metrics) are not documented. Validation is implicitly achieved through **real-time data synchronization** via ActiveMQ, with no formal uncertainty quantification or error correction mechanisms described. Quality assurance processes rely on **prerecorded data** in virtual machine images, ensuring consistency during deployment but lacking dynamic validation protocols.', 'Air Quality Management': 'Fidelity considerations in the Air Quality Management twin are centered on **simulation and prediction accuracy** for pollutant dispersion modeling. Validation is achieved through **comparative analysis** of real-time sensor data (PM2.5, temperature, humidity) against simulated outputs, though no explicit uncertainty quantification or error correction mechanisms are detailed. Quality assurance is tied to Azure\u2019s pipeline infrastructure, with no mention of manual or automated validation thresholds.', 'Lab Scale Gantry Crane': 'The gantry crane digital twin incorporates a **Continuous Validation Service** that dynamically compares executed trajectories with simulated kinematic models, enforcing an **acceptable threshold** for deviation. Fidelity is ensured through **real-time sensor feedback** (Swing Angle Encoder, Anemometer) and **operator notifications** for deviations, rather than automated corrections. Uncertainty sources include environmental factors (e.g., wind) and sensor noise, but no formal quantification (e.g., confidence intervals) is provided. Error correction is manual, with operators intervening based on validation alerts.'}